    • selfOpeningBalance

      public boolean selfOpeningBalance()
      Should we use Self-Opening Balance?

      This is required when opening balances should be created by a self reference. Generally not used since the resulting opening balance is not assigned to any category.

      Returns:
      true/false

    • useInvestmentHolding4Category

      public boolean useInvestmentHolding4Category()
      Should we use Holding account for investments when using transfer for category?

      Generally required since QIF does not provide a mechanism for non-transfers into the portfolio account, and hence TaxCredits and Inheritance cannot be achieved correctly without using a holding account

      Returns:
      true/false

    • useMiscIncX4TaxCredit

      public boolean useMiscIncX4TaxCredit()
      Can we use MiscIncX for Reinvested TaxCredit?

      The Tax Credit for a re-invested dividend must be extracted from the security using MiscInc. Ideally we use MiscIncX to directly assign the value to the TaxCredit category. This is not always available and instead we must use MiscInc and then either Cash or the holding account

      Returns:
      true/false

    • useStockSplit

      public boolean useStockSplit()
      Should we provide true stock splits?

      Some programs do not support the StockSplit operation and hence require stock splits to be represented by StockAdjustments

      Returns:
      true/false

    • canTradeZeroShares

      public boolean canTradeZeroShares()
      Can we buy zero shares?

      Some programs do not allow you to buy/sell zero shares, in order to directly add to the cost. In this case we must buy/sell a single share and then perform an adjustment.

      Returns:
      true/false

    • canReturnCapital

      public boolean canReturnCapital()
      Can we return capital?

      Some programs do not allow you to return capital, treating such an event as a dividend as opposed to a return of capital. In this case we must treat it as a sale of zero shares.

      Returns:
      true/false

    • canXferPortfolio

      public boolean canXferPortfolio()
      Can we transfer to/from the portfolio account?

      Some programs do not allow you to perform a transfer using the investment transfer types XIn/XOut and the consolidated types BuyX/SellX/RtrnCapX/DivX etc. In this case the transfer has to be driven from the partner account.

      Returns:
      true/false

    • escapePrices

      public boolean escapePrices()
      Should we escape prices?

      Some programs require prices in price records to be escaped with quotes. Others insist on no escaping.

      Returns:
      true/false
